definitions.definition: The point in the launch of a rocket or an aircraft where it leaves contact with the ground.
examples: we have liftoff [in narration of launches]

definitions.definition: The point at which a person or animal leaves the ground, as for example when jumping .
The point of launching into success or action.

main_definition: ( aerospace ) The point in the launch of a rocket or an aircraft where it leaves contact with the ground.
secondary_definitions: The point at which a person or animal leaves the ground, as for example when jumping .
( figurative ) The point of launching into success or action.
